<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0" width="100%">
<tr bgcolor="#5B96D8">
<td align="left" width="100%"><font face="verdana,trebuchet,sans-serif" color="white" style="font-size: 11px; font-weight: bold;">EARTHDAWN(R) GOES "DOWN UNDER"</font></td>
</tr>
<tr bgcolor="#5B96D8">
<td width="100%">
<p align="right">
<i><font face="verdana,trebuchet,sans-serif" color="#ffffff" style="font-size: 11px; font-weight: bold;">By James Flowers,
          16 October 2003</font></i>
</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr bgcolor="#7EB4FA">
<td align="left" width="100%"><font face="verdana,trebuchet,sans-serif" color="black" style="font-size: 11px">
<p>
<b>(Auckland, New Zealand) [October 16, 2003] - RedBrick Limited announced today that they have successfully concluded negotiations for an EARTHDAWN(R) licence with FASA Corporation.</b>
</p>

<p>"To say we're excited about this would be an understatement!" said Richard Vowles, RedBrick Director and Projects Manager. "We have been working with both FASA Corporation and key members of the online EARTHDAWN(R) community for a number of months. Now we are able to publicly move forward with our plans for the EARTHDAWN(R) property."</p>

<p>James Flowers, RedBrick Director and Line Developer said, "We have an ambitious schedule ahead of us. Our licence allows us to take the EARTHDAWN(R) reins and drive forward from the base that FASA Corporation firmly established with the First Edition game line during the 90's. We are looking forward to not only producing a series of high-quality rulebooks and supplements for the EARTHDAWN(R) game line, but also fully supporting the game online via the Internet and, over time, with a range of merchandise and miniatures."</p>

<p>RedBrick's products will be based on the First Edition of FASA Corporation's EARTHDAWN(R) epic fantasy roleplaying game. James Flowers explained, "We didn't want to change the First Edition rules because we felt that nothing was fundamentally broken. It was a conscious decision on our part to ensure that our materials are 100% compatible with the First Edition materials currently in print. While we intend to reprint out-of-print supplements, we will be ensuring that these products are updated to include new content and errata."</p>

<p>When asked about the response from the online fan-base, Richard Vowles replied, "So far it's been extremely enthusiastic. We have had a lot of interest from those who have been working with us to date, providing feedback, criticism and direction. It is an absolute 'must' that we actively engage the EARTHDAWN(R) community in our publishing decisions, and that is one of our earliest goals. We are looking forward to receiving submissions from artists and writers alike in due course."</p>

<p>More information will be made available at: <a target="_blank" href="http://www.earthdawnclassic.com">http://www.earthdawn-classic.com</a>
</p>

<p>EARTHDAWN(R) is a Registered Trademark of FASA Corporation. All Rights Reserved. RedBrick Limited is located "down under" in New Zealand, well-known world-wide as the country in which "The Lord of the Rings(tm)" movies were filmed, and now the home of the Fourth World!</p>
</font></td>
</tr>
<td align="right" width="100%"><font face="verdana,trebuchet,sans-serif" color="black" style="font-size: 11px" size="-1"><a href="http://www.earthdawn-classic.com:80/readMore.html?id=61">Go back to article</a></font></td>
</table>
