<tr bgcolor="#5B96D8">
<td width="20%"><font face="verdana,trebuchet,sans-serif" color="#ffffff" style="font-size: 11px; font-weight: bold;"><b>Author</b></font></td><td width="80%"><font face="verdana,trebuchet,sans-serif" color="#ffffff" style="font-size: 11px; font-weight: bold;"><b>Discussion</b></font></td>
</tr>
</table>
<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0" width="100%">
<tr bgcolor="#7EB4FA">
<td valign="top" width="20%"><font face="verdana,trebuchet,sans-serif" color="black" style="font-size: 11px"><b>warren99</b>
<br>19 October 2003</font></td><td width="80%"><font><b>Earthdawn miniatures</b>
<br>
<p>I do wish you every success in this - it doesn't matter which company promotes Earthdawn be it 1st or 2nd edition rules - just so long as Earthdawn is still alive!!

However, it has come to my attention that although new books, new disciplines and new characters are developed there does seem to be a gaping hole where miniatures are concerned. Heartbreaker did a great job with there now OOP selection of Earthdawn stuff and Ral Partha did a few - but that seems to be it!  Is there anybody out there that could produce more miniatures for Earthdawn?  It would seem a shame not to produce new stuff - what about horrors?  Sofar there are only two horrors available in a Heartbreaker blister #311 as well as a despairthought #331 and a couple of wormskulls in the #328 blister.  With all the nasties around in Earthdawn literature it would be nice to have more horrors, monsters, Therans, and even blood elves to paint up and use during gaming sessions.  I realise that many Earthdawn players do not utilise minis in game play but my game group prefer to so that there is some tangible identification.

Come on someone there are many people with money to burn on this - just check out ebay and see the ridiculous amounts of money spent on such OOP miniatures (yeah alright I'm guilty too!)

best of luck with your literary quests, but spare a thought to those that love the representative minis.... (please?)

Woz</p>
</font></td>
</tr>
</table>
<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0" width="100%">
<tr bgcolor="#A0D5FF">
<td valign="top" width="20%"><font face="verdana,trebuchet,sans-serif" color="black" style="font-size: 11px"><b>James Flowers</b>
<br>19 October 2003</font></td><td width="80%"><font><b>Earthdawn miniatures</b>
<br>
<p>Hi Woz. We have miniatures on the radar, and are able to produce these under the terms of our license. However, it's still early days for RedBrick and we need to do more work on determining how best to handle this, and who to work with. Heartbreaker are no longer, so the likelihood of bring back their line is slim-to-none. Ral Partha are still a possibility, but yet to be approached. Please be assured that this isn't just a literary exercise, but there are priorities to be determined and a miniatures line will need to be able to be financially sustainable as well. Short answer? Miniatures? Yes, absolutely. When, who and how? Not sure yet...</p>
</font></td>
</tr>
</table>
 
</td><td valign="top" width="15%">
